profile_data.summary:
I'm a Materials Engineer with 6+ years of experience in research and development in both academic and Silicon Valley companies, primarily focused on nanotechnology and novel nanomaterials synthesis for different applications.  I've developed strong analytical and problem solving skill, plus an intuition in data throughout my research journey.  I'm passionate about machine learning, using AI for prediction and facilitating data analysis, love challenges and am a fast learner.  I have successfully developed a novel nanopatterning method for a desired pitch length within a year utilizing electroplating, a technique that is completely new to me when I joined the company.

Besides my engineering background, I also have an MBA and have been working in Business development field for a few years.  My duty included explore and develop new business opportunities, strategic planning, and potential business analysis, etc.

projects.description: DeepFake image classification with CNN and MobileNetV2 using TensorFlow Keras on the Kaggle dataset consisting of 10,000 images for both fake and real faces.  The dataset is split at 0.8/0.1/0.1 (train/test/valid ratio) and the CNN with 3 convolution layers model achieved an accuracy of 90% while the MobileNetV2 achieved an accuracy of only 50% due to overfitting.

projects.description: A research report on the online battery estimation using Deep Convolution Neural Network (DCNN).  With DCNN, the online estimation of the state of charge of the lithium ion battery can be estimated using the measurements of the charge capacity, current, and voltage during a partial charge cycle. This model is also capable to approximate the state of health of the battery cells. Furthermore, this can extend to the SOC and SOH of the battery for electric vehicle.
projects.title: A Deep Learning Approach for Battery Lifetime Online Estimation
